      "content": "thanks. So, looking at both sides, it feels like the pro-regulation side's argument basically boils down to \"we need to protect people from things we don't like.\" On the other hand, the libertarian view seems rooted in these much deeper, more fundamental principles about human autonomy. Do you think the pro-regulation arguments actually hold up against those philosophical foundations, or are they just more reactionary/practical responses?",
